  12,52,"[Then Yûsuf (Joseph) said: ",footnotes:1:[{12:52}.]
  12,53,""
  12,54,"And the king said: "
  13,19,"Shall he then who knows that what has been revealed unto you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه و سلم) from your Lord is the truth be like him who is blind? But it is only the men of understanding that pay heed."
  13,20,"Those who fulfil the Covenant of Allâh and break not the Mîthâq (bond, treaty, covenant)."
  13,21,"And those who join that which Allâh has commanded to be joined (i.e. they are good to their relatives and do not sever the bond of kinship), and fear their Lord, and dread the terrible reckoning (i.e. abstain from all kinds of sins and evil deeds which Allâh has forbidden and perform all kinds of good deeds which Allâh has ordained)."